The Objection of Aerius: For what reaſon do you commemorate after Death, the Names of thoſe that are departed? He that is alive prayeth, or maketh Diſpenſation (of the Myſteries) what ſhall the Dead be profited hereby? And if the Prayer of thoſe here do altogether (
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ) profit them that be there; then let no body be Godly;


                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉

                   let no Man do Good; but let him procure ſome Friends, by what means it pleaſeth him, either by perſuading them by Money, or intreating Friends at his Death; and let them pray for him, that he may ſuffer nothing there; and that thoſe inexpiable Sins, which he hath committed, may not be required at his hands. p. 238.
